        answer: { en: 'Mars (Mangal) rules Scorpio in Vedic astrology. While Western astrology assigns Pluto as co-ruler, traditional Jyotish uses only visible planets. Mars in Scorpio operates very differently from Mars in Aries — here it is internalized, strategic, and psychologically focused rather than overtly aggressive. Ketu is also considered a co-significator, adding depth and mystical quality.', hi: 'वैदिक ज्योतिष में मंगल (मंगल) वृश्चिक राशि का स्वामी है। मेष में मंगल से बहुत अलग — यहाँ यह आंतरिक, रणनीतिक और मनोवैज्ञानिक रूप से केंद्रित है। केतु को सह-कारक माना जाता है, जो गहराई और रहस्यमय गुणवत्ता जोड़ता है।', sa: 'वैदिकज्योतिषे मङ्गलः वृश्चिकराशेः स्वामी अस्ति। मेषे मङ्गलात् बहु भिन्नम् — अत्र मङ्गलः बाह्याक्रमणस्य स्थाने आन्तरिकशक्तेः, गुप्तान्वेषणस्य, परिवर्तनस्य च ग्रहः भवति। सः वृश्चिकजातेभ्यः तीव्रां भावनात्मिकगम्भीरताम्, अन्वेषणशक्तिम्, सङ्कटेषु अपारं शौर्यं च प्रयच्छति।', mai: 'वैदिक ज्योतिष में मंगल (मंगल) वृश्चिक राशि का स्वामी है। मेष में मंगल से बहुत अलग — यहाँ यह आंतरिक, रणनीतिक और मनोवैज्ञानिक रूप से केंद्रित है। केतु को सह-कारक माना जाता है, जो गहराई और रहस्यमय गुणवत्ता जोड़ता है।', mr: 'वैदिक ज्योतिष में मंगल (मंगल) वृश्चिक राशि का स्वामी है। मेष में मंगल से बहुत अलग — यहाँ यह आंतरिक, रणनीतिक और मनोवैज्ञानिक रूप से केंद्रित है। केतु को सह-कारक माना जाता है, जो गहराई और रहस्यमय गुणवत्ता जोड़ता है।', ta: 'Mars (Mangal) rules Scorpio in Vedic astrology. While Western astrology assigns Pluto as co-ruler, traditional Jyotish uses only visible planets. Mars in Scorpio operates very differently from Mars in Aries — here it is internalized, strategic, and psychologically focused rather than overtly aggressive. Ketu is also considered a co-significator, adding depth and mystical quality.', te: 'Mars (Mangal) rules Scorpio in Vedic astrology. While Western astrology assigns Pluto as co-ruler, traditional Jyotish uses only visible planets. Mars in Scorpio operates very differently from Mars in Aries — here it is internalized, strategic, and psychologically focused rather than overtly aggressive. Ketu is also considered a co-significator, adding depth and mystical quality.', bn: 'Mars (Mangal) rules Scorpio in Vedic astrology. While Western astrology assigns Pluto as co-ruler, traditional Jyotish uses only visible planets. Mars in Scorpio operates very differently from Mars in Aries — here it is internalized, strategic, and psychologically focused rather than overtly aggressive. Ketu is also considered a co-significator, adding depth and mystical quality.', kn: 'Mars (Mangal) rules Scorpio in Vedic astrology. While Western astrology assigns Pluto as co-ruler, traditional Jyotish uses only visible planets. Mars in Scorpio operates very differently from Mars in Aries — here it is internalized, strategic, and psychologically focused rather than overtly aggressive. Ketu is also considered a co-significator, adding depth and mystical quality.', gu: 'Mars (Mangal) rules Scorpio in Vedic astrology. While Western astrology assigns Pluto as co-ruler, traditional Jyotish uses only visible planets. Mars in Scorpio operates very differently from Mars in Aries — here it is internalized, strategic, and psychologically focused rather than overtly aggressive. Ketu is also considered a co-significator, adding depth and mystical quality.' }
